comment: When Johnny says, "You never existed," he's absolutely right. The person he fell in love with doesn't exist and never will. It's heartbreaking and life altering to realize that the person you married and love so much doesn't exist and no matter what you do they never will. It was all an act. I actually said the same thing to my future ex-husband. Some parts of their audio tapes were hard to hear because it was like listening to my ex and I. It made me realize that I haven't recovered as much as I thought.  My ex used not just the same manipulative tactics as Amber, but literally some of the same verbiage. We had not only had similar arguments/discussions/battles, some parts were the exact same. In my opinion, Amber is a textbook Covert Narcissist and the Queen of Projection.  Suddenly a few years ago Johnny was barely recognizable. He was extremely thin, frail and looked like he was on his death bed. I think this was because she had drained the life out of him. He literally was a shell of the person he once was. I lost 40 pounds, without wanting to, in 3 months. I looked like I was dying and some days thought I was and my body was going to just shut down. This type of abuse harms you in every way possible. It's a kind of hell that nobody should go through.
